Package de.mslab.ciphers.helpers

Provides helper classes which count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CipherHelper
    Marker interface, so that we can combine the functionality of DifferentialComparator and DifferentialActiveComponentsCounter in a single CipherHelper class for each cipher.
    DifferentialComparator
    Compares two differentials for independency, that means, if they share active bits or active bytes.
    RecomputedOperationsCounter
    Count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers.

Package de.mslab.ciphers.helpers Description

Provides helper classes which count the number of active bits or bytes in non-linear operations in the matching phase for the individual block ciphers. The point of non-linear operations differs from cipher to cipher depending on where non-linear operations occur in the round functions.
